observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
Require the GSO-Designate and the Municipal Assessor to exert effort in the retrieval of land titles and other necessary documents as basis to establish ownership and determine proper valuation;
Allocate adequate budget for the titling of the subject land properties in the name of the Municipal Government of Mandaon to establish absolute ownership and reduce the risk of third-party claims;
Make representations with the Land Registration Authority or Registry of Deeds to confirm the ownership of all land properties covered by the Tax Declaration on hand and thereafter, secure copies of the Torrens Title or any equivalent document relative thereto; and
Direct the Municipal Accountant to properly account all the land properties of the Municipality using the cost or fair value and effect the necessary adjustments in the books to arrive at a more reliable Land account balance in accordance with IPSAS 17 or any other applicable accounting standards.

